cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and word embeddings. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a probabilistic model for learning domain-specific word embeddings. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with organizing text into hierarchical domains, and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing models for language understanding. Finally, it could also be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with analyzing large real-world review datasets.
